+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KyHVqB8hnzbWNs75grUMYn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 34 tests pass, build compiles, and lint is clean. Here's a summary of the 6 bugs found and fixed:\n\n### Bug 1: `OrderRepository.update` — missing field merge\n**File:** `src/orders/repository.ts:38`\n**Problem:** `update()` created a new object from only the `updates` parameter, discarding all existing fields.\n**Fix:** Changed `{ ...updates, id, updatedAt }` to `{ ...existing, ...updates, id, updatedAt }`.\n\n### Bug 2: `calculateOrderTotal` — premature rounding of intermediates\n**File:** `src/billing/calculator.ts:20-23`\n**Problem:** Intermediate values (discountAmount, afterDiscount, taxAmount) were rounded before being used in subsequent calculations, causing accumulated rounding errors (130.87 instead of 130.86).\n**Fix:** Compute all intermediates without rounding; only round the final output values in the return object.\n\n### Bug 3: `BillingService.registerHandlers` — unbound `handleRefund`\n**File:** `src/billing/service.ts:25`\n**Problem:** `handleRefund` was registered as an event handler without `.bind(this)`, so `this.payments` was undefined when the handler fired.\n**Fix:** Changed `this.handleRefund` to `this.handleRefund.bind(this)`.\n\n### Bug 4: `EventBus` — global handler registry\n**File:** `src/events/bus.ts:4`\n**Problem:** Event handlers were stored in a module-level `globalHandlers` map shared across all `EventBus` instances, causing cross-test pollution.\n**Fix:** Moved the handlers map to an instance property `private handlers`.\n\n### Bug 5: `InventoryService.handleOrderCancelled` — bogus status guard\n**File:** `src/inventory/service.ts:50`\n**Problem:** The handler checked `eventWithItems.status !== 'cancelled'` and returned early, but the cancellation event emitted by `OrderService` never includes a `status` field, so stock was never released.\n**Fix:** Removed the spu